        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 12:44PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 1244 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cranfills Gap, or 13 miles northeast of Hamilton, moving east at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Cranfills Gap around 1250 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Pancake, Cayote, Cedar
Shores, Whiteway, Aleman, Hurst Springs, Womack, Lakewood Harbor,
Jonesboro, and Norse.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
